  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Distress monitoring is an important issue in cancer survivors. However, conventional distress
      screening is very difficult to perform. This study investigates the efficacy of wearable
      device as a tool of distress monitoring in breast cancer survivors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
